    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Actually this is in the contract of the API that `nbPages`, `nbHits`, `page` and `hitsPerPage` are always returned and a number. Therefore conditional fake responses should have those keys as well, and our documentation includes those keys already.\r\n\r\nNo further action is needed as this didn't come up for other people.",
